3. Add the two launchd-wrapper tripwires (content hash + hook-log assertion).
4. Run probed/clean/probed on the next three scheduled gaa wake-ups.
5. If 3/3 pass: leave hook in place, open follow-on for `Bash` policy. If any fail: `rm` the hook file, postmortem the deviation.

Heated-debate MCP pilot remains rejected: it adds machinery to retest `context.txt` behavior that already works.

